&gt;correctly
&gt;		
&gt;		MyProgram word = new MyProgram(&quot;Word&quot;, MyProgram.WORDPROCESSOR);

This is a new local variable named &quot;word&quot;. You want to assign to the
already-declared field &quot;word&quot;.

I do this from time to time. Try this:

                 word = new MyProgram(&quot;Word&quot;, MyProgram.WORDPROCESSOR);

and do the same for the others.

